{"word":"G3501 - νέος - néos - neh'-os - New","slug":"G3501","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">νέος</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>néos"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>neh'-os"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>New"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BD;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03BF;&#x03C2;, &#x03BD;&#x03B5;&#x03C9;&#x0301;&#x03C4;&#x03B5;&#x03C1;&#x03BF;&#x03C2; - neos  neo&#x0304;teros</b> - <i>neh'-os, neh-o'-ter-os</i><p/>A primary word, including the comparative (second form); &ldquo;new&rdquo;, that is, (of persons) <i>youthful</i>, or (of things) <i>fresh</i>; figuratively <i>regenerate:</i> - new, young."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3502\">G3502</a>, <a href=\"#/G3503\">G3503</a>, <a href=\"#/G3504\">G3504</a>, <a href=\"#/G3555\">G3555</a>, <a href=\"#/G3556\">G3556</a>"}]}